Citation.sTitle: Density and Viscosity Experimental Data of the Ternary Mixtures 1-Propanol or 2-Propanol + Water + 1-Ethyl-3-methylimidazolium Ethylsulfate. Correlation and Prediction of Physical Properties of the Ternary Systems
Citation.sAbstract: In this paper, we have determined densities, F, refractive indices, nD, and dynamic viscosities, c, of two ternary mixtures, 1-propanol + water + 1-ethyl-3-methylimidazolium ethylsufate (EMISE) and 2-propanol + water + EMISE, at 298.15 K over the whole composition range and at atmospheric pressure. Excess molar volumes, VE, refractive index deviations, AnD, viscosity deviations, Ac, and excess free energies of activation of viscous flow, AG*E, have been calculated from experimental data and fitted to Cibulka and Singh et al. equations. The excess properties have been used to test several prediction models.
